TopicTitle: Crashing on finish loading. Not sure which mod is causing it?

Articles.Content:
Hi guys, I just finished adding some mods and I'm not sure what's causing the game to crash.

The first line in the error.log is

"mono.dll caused an Access Violation (0xc0000005)
  in module mono.dll at 0033:3dab0e18."

Here's a link to the error.log https://pastebin.com/2gUUa760

And the output_log.txt  https://mega.nz/#!puYRybqD!497C9OEiNJCAw0WLXAfhpYprxsYqLoIT08YQ059n0fM

crash.dmp https://mega.nz/#!N2wk0ISb!KzcZ8K-4FGfV08YNCGfP-1SKwUtVRXVndzF_ZscUbN8 (I don't even know how to read these?)

 

Any ideas?

 

Edited October 26, 2017 by Tetsuoken

mono.dll errors tend to be caused by incompatible mods.

You have a large amount of mods installed. I would check to make sure that each one is compatible with KSP v1.3.1. Keep in mind that mods in KSP are not forwards/backwards compatible, so a mod that is compatible with 1.3.0 isn't necessarily compatible with 1.3.1. 

A good way to find out if each mod is compatible is to go the forum thread for the mod. Or you can pinpoint which mod is causing the crashing by removing half of your mods and testing. If it crashes, you know the troublemaker isn't in the half you removed, and vice versa.

That's a good idea, the removing half part, I'll do that and keep narrowing it down. Thanks for the tip.

 

EDIT: It was kOS that was causing the problem, I had an outdated version. d'oh.
